## Before the Sections

### Binding Constraint

The binding constraint is **data integrity across versioned targets**. Every meaningful number in the system — whether a metric is off-track, whether revenue is at-risk, what a historical report shows — depends on looking up the right target for the right period. If the effective-date lookup logic is wrong anywhere, reports silently show incorrect status flags with no visible error. Every architecture decision around transactions, the domain logic layer, and the prohibition on overwriting target rows exists to protect this.

### Changes from the PRD

| PRD says | Architecture says | Why |
|---|---|---|
| PDF generation uses "print-to-PDF or a server-side rendering library" | `@react-pdf/renderer` specifically, via a dedicated `/api/report/pdf` server-side route | Eliminates browser print dialog; gives full layout control; no external service dependency |
| Stack TBD (OQ-4) | Next.js 14 + PostgreSQL 15 + Prisma + Railway | Resolves OQ-4. Single-repo full-stack eliminates a separate API server; Railway eliminates devops overhead |

