## 1. System Overview

Impact Dashboard is a single-process, single-database web application. A Next.js 14 server handles both page rendering and data mutations; PostgreSQL (via Prisma ORM) is the sole data store; NextAuth.js enforces session-based authentication with role-based route protection at the middleware layer. There are no background workers, no queues, and no external API calls in v1. The one exception to synchronous page rendering is PDF export, which is a server-side API route that builds a report from a database query, renders it with `@react-pdf/renderer`, and streams the binary result to the browser.

