**Module rules:**

- `app/` modules are thin — validate input, call `lib/`, format response. No business logic lives here.
- `lib/domain/` functions are pure — they accept plain data and return a result. No database calls, no side effects. This makes them independently testable.
- `lib/domain/` never imports from `app/`. It may import from `lib/` siblings only for shared types.
- `components/reports/` uses `@react-pdf/renderer` primitives only — no HTML elements, no Tailwind classes.
- `middleware.ts` is the only place role-to-route enforcement lives. It is not duplicated in individual page components.

