## 5. Request & Event Flows

### 5.1 Page request (standard)

All standard page requests are synchronous Server Component renders. Example: ED loads `/dashboard`.

```
1. Browser GETs /dashboard
2. middleware.ts reads session cookie → verifies role = 'ed' → passes
3. dashboard/page.tsx (Server Component) runs:
   a. fetchProgramOutcomes() → Prisma query → PostgreSQL
   b. fetchRevenueData() → Prisma query → PostgreSQL (entries + targets, all funder/categories)
   c. fetchFunderDeadlines() → Prisma query → PostgreSQL
4. Domain logic applied to results:
   a. isOffTrack() called per metric entry
   b. revenueStatus() called per funder/category row (per-funder status badges)
   c. orgRevenueStatus() called once on all entries + targets (org-wide summary figure)
   d. deadlineWindow() called per funder
5. HTML rendered server-side and streamed to browser
```

### 5.2 PDF export

The one async-feeling flow (it's still synchronous — just slower).

```
1. User submits /report form (report type, period, funder id, ED notes)
2. Browser POSTs to /api/report/pdf
3. middleware.ts verifies session and role
4. pdf/route.ts:
   a. Validates request body
   b. If funder report: checks funder has linked programs → 422 if not
   c. Runs report query via Prisma
   d. Passes result to BoardReport.tsx or FunderReport.tsx
   e. @react-pdf/renderer renders the component tree to PDF bytes
   f. Returns binary stream with Content-Type: application/pdf
5. Browser receives PDF → download or new tab
```

### 5.3 Data mutation (example: staff submits metric entry)

```
1. Staff submits entry form at /programs/[id]/entry
2. Browser POSTs to /api/programs/[id]/entry (API Route)
3. middleware.ts verifies role = 'staff' and session.programId matches [id]
4. Route handler validates fields — blank = field-level error, stop
5. Prisma creates metric_entries row with entered_by, entered_at, period, actual_value
6. Returns success; page redirects back to form with submitted values shown read-only
```

### 5.4 Metric creation (admin — transactional)

```
1. Admin submits metric form with target value + effective_from
2. Server validates: both target fields required
3. prisma.$transaction([metric.create, metricTarget.create])
   → if either fails, both roll back
4. Admin sees new metric in list with its initial target
```

