## 6. Interface Contracts

### 6.1 Internal API routes

| Route | Method | Caller | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| `/api/auth/[...nextauth]` | GET / POST | NextAuth.js internals | Session management |
| `/api/report/pdf` | POST | `/report` page | Generate and return PDF binary |

**`/api/report/pdf` request body:**

```typescript
{
  reportType: 'board' | 'funder';
  period: string;          // "YYYY-MM" — converted to period date server-side
  funderId?: string;       // required when reportType = 'funder'
  edNotes?: string;        // max 300 words, validated server-side
}
```

**`/api/report/pdf` responses:**

| Status | Meaning |
|---|---|
| 200 | PDF binary stream (`Content-Type: application/pdf`) |
| 400 | Validation failure (missing required field) |
| 401 | Not authenticated |
| 403 | Role not permitted to generate this report type |
| 422 | Funder report requested but funder has no linked programs |

### 6.2 External services

None in v1. The PRD explicitly excludes all external API integrations.

### 6.3 Session contract

The NextAuth session object carries:

```typescript
{
  user: {
    id: string;
    role: 'ed' | 'fundraising' | 'staff' | 'admin';
    programId: string | null;  // non-null for staff only
  }
}
```

`middleware.ts` and all server-side data fetches read from this object. It is the only source of identity truth at runtime.

