## 7. Cross-Cutting Patterns

### 7.1 Authentication

NextAuth.js Credentials provider. On login, credentials are checked against `password_hash` (bcrypt). On success, an encrypted `httpOnly`, `Secure` session cookie is set with a 30-day TTL. No tokens are exposed to client-side JavaScript.

### 7.2 Authorisation

`middleware.ts` at the project root is the single enforcement point. It runs before every request — both page loads and API Route calls. Logic:

- No valid session → redirect to `/login`
- Valid session, wrong role for route → redirect to `/login`
- Staff role → redirect to `/programs/[session.programId]/entry` regardless of requested route
- Staff accessing `/programs/[id]/entry` where `[id] ≠ session.programId` → redirect to own program

**Role-to-route table (authoritative).** This table is the source of truth for `middleware.ts` implementation. Every row is an enforced rule, not a UI convention.

| Route pattern | Permitted roles | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `/login` | All (unauthenticated) | Redirect to role landing if already authenticated |
| `/dashboard` | `ed` | — |
| `/report` | `ed`, `fundraising` | — |
| `/funders` | `ed`, `fundraising` | — |
| `/funders/[id]` | `ed`, `fundraising` | — |
| `/revenue` | `fundraising` | — |
| `/programs/[id]/entry` | `staff` | `[id]` must match `session.programId`; redirect own program if mismatch |
| `/admin` | `admin` | — |
| `/admin/[section]` | `admin` | — |
| `/api/report/pdf` | `ed`, `fundraising` | API Route — middleware enforces before handler runs |
| `/api/*` (all other routes) | Checked per route | No API route is unauthenticated in v1 |

**Server Actions are not used for mutations.** See ADR-007. All form submissions POST to API Routes. This ensures middleware runs on every write operation without requiring per-action session checks.

### 7.3 Error handling

**Field-level errors** (missing required input): returned as structured validation errors, displayed inline beside the field. Never as a page-level toast or alert.

**Business rule violations** (e.g. deleting a metric with existing entries, funder report with no linked programs): returned as a specific error message. The UI surfaces the message and the correct next action (e.g. "Deactivate instead").

**Missing data in reports**: never blank, never zero. Display "No data entered" per PRD §11 rules.

**Unexpected server errors**: return a generic error page. Do not expose stack traces.

### 7.4 Secrets and environment variables

| Variable | Purpose | Where set |
|---|---|---|
| `DATABASE_URL` | Prisma connection string | Railway (injected automatically) |
| `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` | Session cookie encryption key | Railway (manual — generate with `openssl rand -base64 32`) |
| `NEXTAUTH_URL` | App's public URL | Railway (manual) |

No secrets in source code. No `.env` files committed to the repository.

### 7.5 Passwords

Stored as bcrypt hashes only. The `password_hash` column on the `users` table. Plaintext is never logged, stored, or transmitted after the login request.

