## 15. Future Evolution Hooks

Compartmentalisation decisions made now so future extensions don't require a rewrite. No code is spent on them.

| Hook | What was done now | Future extension enabled |
|---|---|---|
| `lib/domain/` is pure logic | No database dependency in domain functions | AI-assisted narrative (PRD §8) can call the same functions for context |
| Form field names match DB column names | Fields named consistently with schema | Data import (Google Sheets CSV, CRM sync) can pre-populate forms without changing components |
| `components/reports/` isolated | PDF components are self-contained | Funder-mandated templates (OQ-5) are new components in the same folder, not changes to existing ones |
| Versioned target tables | `effective_from` pattern already in schema | Mid-year target changes, multi-year historical reporting — no schema change needed |
| Auth in `middleware.ts` only | Role-to-route logic is in one file | Multi-tenancy would require adding `org_id` to tables and queries — significant, but current code doesn't actively resist it |
| `@react-pdf/renderer` in isolated components | PDF logic doesn't touch page components | Additional report templates (foundation-mandated formats) add a new component without touching existing ones |

